The paper deals with the security analysis of Feistel ciphers, which is a topic in cryptography and falls under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of key-schedules and their impact on security, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of efficient transformations and round-functions also suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
